<p>73  France<br/>16/9/17<br/>My Dear Father &amp; Mother,<br/>A line only to say how delighted I was to get you letters of 10th amp; 11th July.  It has been a long spell without any home news.<br/>We are up to our eyes in preparation for an offensive, which we hope will give the Hun a big kick.  The news of Uncle Toms illness is most distressing but I trust next mail will</p>
